HematoVision: Advanced Blood Cell Classification Using Transfer Learning Project Description HematoVision is a deep learning-based web application that classifies different types of blood cells from microscopic images using transfer learning techniques. The system helps in automatically identifying blood cell types, which can assist in medical diagnosis and laboratory analysis. This project uses a pre-trained Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model and applies transfer learning to improve classification accuracy while reducing training time. Objectives To classify blood cell images into different categories. To apply transfer learning using a pre-trained deep learning model. To build a user-friendly web interface for uploading images and viewing predictions. To achieve high accuracy with efficient model performance. Technologies Used Python TensorFlow / Keras Transfer Learning (MobileNetV2 / ResNet50) Flask (Web Framework) HTML, CSS NumPy, OpenCV Blood Cell Types Classified Red Blood Cells (RBC) White Blood Cells (WBC) Platelets Other subtypes (if dataset includes) How It Works User uploads a microscopic blood cell image. The image is preprocessed (resized, normalized). The trained transfer learning model predicts the class. The result is displayed on the web interface. Features Image upload functionality Fast prediction system Simple and clean web interface High accuracy using transfer learning Easy to deploy and modify Applications Medical laboratories Disease diagnosis support Educational purposes Research in medical imaging3:41 pm
3:41 pm
HematoVision is a deep learning web application that classifies blood cell images using transfer learning. It uses a pre-trained CNN model to accurately identify different blood cell types. The system includes image upload, preprocessing, and real-time prediction through a simple Flask-based interface, supporting medical analysis and research.3:43 pm
